The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International
                                                                                                                                          17                                    The UK government has apologised to the Pope over official documents that mocked his forthcoming visit to Britain by suggesting he should bless a gay marriage and even launch Papal-branded condoms.                 In a nation where class issues often determine how people vote, David Cameron is campaigning for Prime Minister as an ordinary bloke.                   Stephen Hawking has suggested that aliens almost certainly exist but has warned humanity not to try to contact them.                   -Novelist and poet Alan Sillitoe, one of the Angry Young Men of British fiction has died, media reports said today. He was 82.                                                                                                                                                                                                                             
